A vintage 1970s-style technical illustration depicting a massive industrial gear mechanism with multiple interconnected cogs and wheels, rendered in warm sepia and burnt orange tones on aged cream paper. In the center, a single sleek document card moves through the machinery on a conveyor belt system, being stamped and processed by mechanical arms with precision switches flipping to "true" or "false" positions. The scene evokes an old factory floor with brass fixtures, analog dials, and steam wisps, suggesting systematic optimization and methodical processing. Overhead, a complex network of pneumatic tubes carries small data packets between sorting stations. The composition uses a slight fish-eye perspective to emphasize the overwhelming scale of the mechanical system compared to the humble document being processed.
